## 2026-04-24 (Maps stabilization sprint + Quick Wins audit)

### Shipped (all on `fix/chat-production-hardening`)
- **`9b86f72`** `fix: remove deprecated require-based panel context import`
  - `/apartments/:id` was rendering blank with `ReferenceError: require is not defined`. The deprecated `usePanelContext` shim in `src/components/layout/ThreePanelLayout.tsx` used CommonJS `require()` — Vite/ESM browser builds don't expose it. Migrated `ApartmentDetail`, `CarDetail`, `RestaurantDetail` to import `useThreePanelContext` directly from `@/components/explore/ThreePanelLayout`. Deleted the shim.
- **`c0caa97`** `feat: add apartment availability and booking flow`
  - Multi-step `BookingDialog` (dates → review → success) wired to the "Check Availability" CTA. `ContactHostDialog` pre-fills a friendly inquiry message. Pure pricing engine with **12 unit tests**: `monthly_subtotal + daily_prorate + cleaning_fee = estimated total`. Honors `apartment.minimum_stay_days` + `available_from`/`available_to`. Uses existing `bookings` + `leads` tables — no migration. Anon users fill the form; submit routes to `/login?returnTo=…`. Smoke-verified both inserts via service role.
- **`1a82f97`** + **`c9ea238`** `fix: use valid uuid for anonymous chat conversations`
  - Killed `invalid input syntax for type uuid` + `CHANNEL_ERROR` / `TIMED_OUT` realtime loops. Anon synthetic `conversation.id` is now a pure UUID via `useAnonSession` (`crypto.randomUUID()` polyfill + strict UUID regex on the localStorage value). Realtime gate switched from fragile `id.startsWith('anon-')` to semantically correct `conversation.user_id === user.id`.
- **`e00b872`** `fix: stabilize google maps singleton loader and marker events`
  - **The big one.** Two independent Maps loaders (ChatMap inline bootstrap + GoogleMapView legacy `<script>`) were fighting over the same global, causing "API loaded multiple times" + every `<gmp-map>`/`<gmp-advanced-marker>` failing custom-element re-registration → `gmp-advanced-marker-nondeterministic-duplicate1` deprecation warning. New `src/lib/google-maps-loader.ts` (271 lines, NEW) is the single source of truth. Idempotent across StrictMode + remounts. Detects pre-existing `<script id="google-maps-script">` and reuses it. Public API: `loadGoogleMapsLibrary(name, apiKey)`, `isMapsAuthFailed()`, `onMapsAuthFailed(cb)`. Both ChatMap and GoogleMapView migrated. `marker.addEventListener('gmp-click', …)` + `gmpClickable: true`. Symmetric `removeEventListener` on unmount.
- **`63d3faf`** `fix(maps): pin SDK to quarterly + clearPins on conv switch + a11y on markers`
  - **Quick Win #1**: `params.set('v', import.meta.env.PROD ? 'quarterly' : 'weekly')` — tree-shake-verified; prod bundle only references the quarterly channel. Removes the #1 architectural risk (Google ships breaking changes weekly).
  - **Quick Win #4**: new `useEffect` keyed on `currentConversation?.id` calls `clearPins()` on every conversation switch. No more pin bleed across conversations.
  - **Quick Win #5**: `role="button"`, `aria-label="Open <title>, <label>"`, `aria-current="true"` on the highlighted pin, `aria-hidden` on the decorative emoji.
- **`b054b08`** `feat(maps): add pluggable telemetry hooks`
  - **Quick Win #2**: new `src/lib/maps-telemetry.ts`. 9 discriminated-union event kinds (`script_loaded`, `script_load_failed`, `auth_failed`, `map_init_failed`, `markers_rendered`, `marker_render_failed`, `pin_click`, `fitbounds`, `viewport_idle`, `cluster_expand`). Default sink is structured `console.error`/`console.debug`. Replace once at app boot to forward to Sentry/PostHog: `setMapTelemetrySink((event) => { Sentry.addBreadcrumb({...}); posthog.capture(...); })`. Resilience: `trackMapEvent` swallows sink throws — telemetry must never break the app. **4/4 unit tests** (Vitest with mocked sink). `pin_click` events carry `viaKeyboard` and `newTab` flags, so we'll be able to see Cmd-click and Enter/Space conversions distinctly once a real sink is wired.
- **`ae918f7`** `feat(maps): MarkerClusterer for chat pins`
  - **Quick Win #3**: `@googlemaps/markerclusterer ^2.6.2` (~12 KB raw, ~7 KB gzip). One clusterer per Map. At Medellín-city zoom: pins cluster into numbered bubbles. As user zooms in: clusters fan out into individual price pins. Markers are NEVER constructed with `map: …` — the clusterer owns on-map visibility. `onClusterClick` emits `cluster_expand` telemetry; default zoom-in preserved. Symmetric cleanup: `clusterer.clearMarkers()` after stripping every `gmp-click` listener on unmount.

### Verification audit (2026-04-24)
**21 / 21 verification items pass.** No critical hidden bugs. Three real-but-tolerable yellows (minor): telemetry default sink is `console.debug` (DevTools needs "Verbose" enabled to see); `viewport_idle` event type defined but no emit site yet (wired with "Search this area"); a11y `role="button"` doubles up with native `<gmp-advanced-marker>` button semantics. End-to-end chat smoke from `Origin: https://www.mdeai.co` returns 200 OK + 9 Laureles listings + 2 phase events. Vercel preview deploy state for HEAD: `success`.

